# project.plan

## Project: Consent-Based Emergency Signal Network

## Agent identities
- gpt = ChatGPT project manager / architect / scope / review planning
- cx = local Codex implementation / QA / commit support
- mgpt = mobile ChatGPT planning / mobile review / field notes
- mcx = mobile Codex implementation / mobile test support
- Dennis = owner / product manager / final reviewer

## Operating rule
This file is the central coordination record for project scope, current phase, agent activity, build status, and next actions.
All agents should read this file before work and update it after meaningful work.

---

# 1. Product scope

Build a consent-based safety platform that can support:

1. Mobile app emergency signal snapshot
2. Voluntary emergency witness network
3. BLE / IoT safety device discovery
4. Guardian-authorized emergency case packages
5. Optional cellular IoT fallback for future devices
6. Law-enforcement / verified emergency escalation workflow
7. Privacy, consent, anti-abuse, short retention, and immutable audit logging

Core principle:

> This platform does not provide open-ended covert tracking. It supports consent-based safety, guardian-authorized emergencies, and verified emergency discovery with auditability.

---

# 2. MVP scope

## MVP 1: Local app foundation
Build the first working version locally.

Required:
- App scaffold
- Auth/account placeholder or local profile mode
- Emergency mode screen
- Signal snapshot model
- Local encrypted or structured storage placeholder
- BLE scan abstraction
- Wi-Fi/network context abstraction
- Location permission abstraction
- Snapshot history screen
- Export/debug view for QA
- Clear permission and consent language

## MVP 2: Signal snapshot
A snapshot should eventually include:

- timestamp
- app device ID
- GPS lat/lng/accuracy, when permission granted
- BLE advertisements seen, where OS permits
- Wi-Fi/current network info, where OS permits
- nearby enrolled beacon IDs
- phone/network metadata, where permitted
- emergency_case_id, optional
- retention_expiration timestamp

Raw MAC storage should not be default. Prefer hashed identifiers unless explicitly in verified emergency/legal mode.

## MVP 3: BLE / IoT bridge
Prepare structure for:
- registered BLE safety beacons
- rotating beacon IDs
- RSSI/proximity reading
- emergency beacon matching
- future wearable integration

## MVP 4: Emergency case package
Create data model and placeholder workflow for:

- child/person profile
- guardian profile
- verified emergency state
- known device identifiers
- known BLE/wearable IDs
- known home-network identifiers
- last known snapshots
- audit log

---

# 3. Out of scope for early MVP

Do not build yet:
- real law-enforcement portal
- real AMBER integration
- real cellular carrier brokerage
- ingestible/emission device implementation
- covert tracking
- bypassing OS privacy restrictions
- unauthorized MAC tracking
- raw identifier sharing without emergency/legal controls

---

# 4. Architecture direction

Preferred early stack:
- Mobile: Flutter
- Backend later: Supabase or Firebase
- Local first: build mock/local services before cloud dependency
- Git: all work committed in small, reviewable increments
- CI: add lint/test/build checks once scaffold is stable

Suggested structure:

```text
/lib
  /app
    router.dart
    app.dart
  /core
    /models
    /services
    /permissions
    /storage
    /security
  /features
    /emergency
    /snapshots
    /ble_scanner
    /network_context
    /guardian
    /devices
    /audit
```

