# 6. Privacy and safety requirements

Mandatory:

- consent-first UX
- clear permissions
- no silent tracking
- no open-ended person lookup
- no stalking-enabling feature
- short retention defaults
- emergency escalation must be auditable
- raw identifiers should be minimized, hashed, or protected
- user/guardian authority must be verified before emergency use

Default retention:

- normal snapshots: 24-72 hours
- opt-in family safety: up to 7 days
- active verified emergency: preserve until case closes
- legal hold: only through verified process

# 7. Git workflow

Before work:

- git status
- git branch

During work:

- small changes
- no unrelated refactors
- preserve existing working code
- avoid destructive changes

After work:

- git status
- git diff --check

If available:

- flutter analyze
- flutter test
- flutter build apk

Commit format:

```text
<scope>: <short summary>
```

Examples:

- snapshots: add local signal snapshot model
- emergency: add emergency mode placeholder
- ble: add mock BLE scan service

